column5: Got to marathon around noon yesterday. Check in wasn't until four so jumped on a party boat for a couple hours. The goal is twenty species in a week got four in this trip. Yellowtail snapper, file fish, remora and parrot fish. Jump another charter tomorrow for a full day of Mahi's so excited probably won't sleep much tonight I'm like a kid at Christmas. parrot fish in midair escape.
Wow pretty cool. Wish I was in on this action  Cheers
First is dang well ugly. That second,WOW, what a colour.  How many have asked for the hat? LOL  Keep them coming. Look forward to them.

Two more species off the dock tonight mangrove snapper and pin fish.  Helped a friendly couple from socal land a crazy acrobatic little tarpon. I now know where I am retiring this is truly a fisherman's paradise.
Wicked!  The colour on the second fish is insane!  Id love to see that in person  Catch lots tomorrow!!!!
What a day triple and quadruple headers,  the board behind us isn't even half of of our take today. Arms are sore sunburn is sore. the locals waiting for their take. hope everybody i know is hungry
Three more species as well puts me to nine.  Mahi Mahi, tile fish and snowy groupe and its only Monday.
